queries: This sign can incorporate numbers to show how many goals have been scored.
verbLexeme: 1. To score a goal in Australian rules football.
nominalLexeme: 1. The space into which the players try to get the ball in order to score a point for their team in Australian rules football. English = goal.
2. A point scored by getting the ball to go between the two centre posts in the scoring space in Australian rules football. English = goal.
